{
  "catalog_version": "0.1",
  "_comment": "Curated algebraic laws keyed by canonical name-hint + arity. Attached opt-in via the adapters' --properties flag (ingestion cannot DERIVE laws, only recognise well-known functions). Each emitted law is then checkable by `nl-validator check-properties` against the record's worked examples, so a mis-match that contradicts an example is caught. Property exprs use the predicate-expression vocabulary with the reserved bindings result / arg0..argN. Where possible the law is in the evaluator's DECIDABLE subset (length/eq/le) so consistency can actually be confirmed from examples; involution / functor laws are valid but report UNVERIFIABLE. `match.convention` selects the calling convention: 'function' (free function, e.g. map(f, xs) — collection at arg1) or 'method' (iterator/UFCS method, e.g. xs.map(f) where the receiver is arg0 — collection at arg0); absent means it applies to either (reverse/sort/identity reference arg0 in both conventions).",
  "laws": [
    {
      "id": "law.identity",
      "match": { "name_hints": ["id", "identity"], "arity": 1 },
      "intent_tag": "idempotent",
      "property": {
        "name": "identity",
        "expr": { "kind": "app", "op": "eq", "args": [
          { "kind": "var", "name": "result" },
          { "kind": "var", "name": "arg0" } ] }
      }
    },
    {
